==Ancient Greek==

===Pronunciation===
*φοβέω / phobeō / fob-eh'-o

===Etymology===
*From [[φόβος]] {{GG|5401}};

===Verb===
'''φοβέω'''

# To [[frighten]], that is, (passively) to be alarmed; by analogy to be in awe of, that is, [[revere]]: - be (+ sore) [[afraid]], [[fear]] (exceedingly), [[reverence]].

